    "In an early survey, Stone and Veloso [13] classify MARL based on whether agents communicate and whether agents are homogeneous or not.",
    "6 They view learnable communication as a future research opportunity.",
    "Busoniu et al. [15] consider communication as a means to negotiate action choices and select equilibrium in the research direction of explicit coordination, without further classifying communication.",
    "With the advancement of deep learning, MARL has gradually incorporated deep neural networks such that recent developments are dominated by multi-agent deep reinforcement learning (MADRL).",
